@startuml states-embedder-process
!include ../_includes/style.iuml

title State machine — managed embedder lifecycle (server mode)

' Reflects the logic of embedderLifecycle.ts:
'   - in-flight launch promise = concurrency guard
'   - /v1/models polling = ready check, 60 s budget
'   - silent fallback on any failure (returns null, never throws)
'
' Scope: this is the SERVER mode (resident llama-server --embedding)
' used by interactive routing queries (routeByVectors).
' The CLI mode used by bulk characterization (embedderCli.ts) is NOT
' modelled here as a state machine — every call spawns a fresh
' llama-embedding.exe that exits at the end of the call, so the only
' meaningful states are { idle → spawned → exited } per invocation.
' See components/embedder.puml for the dual-mode component view.

[*] --> Idle

state "Idle (not configured)" as Idle {
  description : routingEmbedderPath empty\nAND routingEmbedderBaseUrl empty.\nRouting falls back to R5 silently.
}

Idle --> Probing : ensureEmbedderReady(filePath)\ncalled by routeByVectors\nor characterizeTree

state "Probing existing" as Probing {
  description : check listRunning() for a\nrunning process with\n`launchedBy: 'embedder'`\n+ same canonical filePath.
}

Probing --> Reused : found alive
Probing --> Launching : not found,\nset in-flight promise

state "Reused" as Reused #FFFDF6 {
  description : return {baseUrl, pid,\nsource:'reused'}.\nCaller proceeds immediately.
}

state "Launching" as Launching {
  description : launchModelByPath(\n  launchedBy:'embedder',\n  customArgs:'--embedding'\n)
}

Launching --> Waiting : spawn OK\n(pid received)
Launching --> Failed : spawn returned !ok\nOR no pid

state "Waiting for /v1/models" as Waiting {
  description : loop until\n• response.ok ⇒ Ready\n• entry.exited ⇒ Crashed\n• 60 s deadline ⇒ Timeout\nPolls every 1 s with 4 s budget per probe.
}

Waiting --> Ready : 200 OK
Waiting --> Crashed : process exited\nduring boot
Waiting --> TimedOut : 60 s deadline

state "Ready" as Ready #FFFDF6 {
  description : return {baseUrl, pid,\nsource:'launched'}.\nVisible in RunningModelsPanel\nunder "embedder" group.
}

state "Crashed" as Crashed {
  description : stopProcess(pid),\nreturn null,\nclear in-flight promise.\nCaller silently falls back to R5.
}

state "Timed out" as TimedOut {
  description : stopProcess(pid),\nreturn null,\nclear in-flight promise.\nCaller silently falls back to R5.
}

state "Failed" as Failed {
  description : log + return null,\nclear in-flight promise.\nCaller silently falls back to R5.
}

Ready --> Idle : stopManagedEmbedders()\nor process killed manually
Crashed --> Idle
TimedOut --> Idle
Failed --> Idle
Reused --> Reused : subsequent\nensureEmbedderReady\n(idempotent)

note bottom of Launching
  Concurrent callers share the SAME
  in-flight promise — never spawn
  twice. This is the only critical
  section in embedderLifecycle.ts.
end note

@enduml
